Rain-polished streets hide a three-way war. **The Calder Civic Trust** poses as a downtown renewal charity—grants, shelters, “clean streets”—but launders bribes and evidence through its legal clinics, arranging scapegoats when donors need sins erased. **Marrowline Security** sells executive protection and camera networks, yet runs a pay-to-vanish surveillance black market, splicing feeds and forging timelines for the highest bidder. **The Gilt Hand Union**, a loose brotherhood of pawn brokers and night buyers, publicly keeps families afloat with cash-for-gold; privately it fences murder tools and trades in favors tied to old debts. Calder bankrolls Marrowline’s tech, Marrowline intimidates Union holdouts, and the Union leaks dirt to burn both—until someone ends up framed.

